<subSubSection id="4953EC89CFB890F5C5A96500E58EFB54" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="41B4A8FD4CB153A7F0C7A6A32A8CA7B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C540DCB22A353053F5D77BFC16BF2448" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
The syntype series was lost during a plane crash when the material loaned to B. H. Lamoral was sent back to Hamburg (label in jar from H. Dastych: &quot;B. H. Lamoral 18.XI.1974; Das ganze Material ist verloren, 1975. Das Flugzeug ist 
<normalizedToken id="2B6B5FE379216F73623ECDA35F86E750" originalValue="abgestürzt”">abgestuerzt&quot;</normalizedToken>
). Lamoral and Reynders (1975: 563) established 
<taxonomicName id="A9ABE510727F56DF6FF5111CCC03C186" authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Opisthophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opisthophthalmus werneri" order="Scorpiones" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="werneri">
<emphasis id="2A9DA77A5744F8FFA3B6F20426AE81C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Opisthophthalmus werneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="E1A1F26BA180427BDF97AA6AAE8DFFD3" genus="O." lsidName="O. pilosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis id="44ED0AC44FF3165173D81F738D9F110B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Werner, 1936 wich is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="133F97DFF0840D349D749472459DD838" genus="O." lsidName="O. pilosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis id="19DDF44AB694B5ED8B26BF030B3810A3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. L. Koch, 1838. 
<bibRefCitation id="960E2EC8DA1BA8778E882D25C48BD842" author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini (2001</bibRefCitation>
: see p.24 for details) later demonstrated that 
<taxonomicName id="540AB82FCF91475988C4B3A1680BAAED" genus="O." lsidName="O. werneri" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="werneri">
<emphasis id="DB9A406566A9287B616A77AEF76A9349" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. werneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="46E459EE3A816DE0D43E644326E3E1ED" authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Opisthophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opisthophthalmus flavescens" order="Scorpiones" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis id="938DE9E54EADE94A64B32DDC22E1C1D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Opisthophthalmus flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Purcell, 1898.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
